# Zod

Validate all untrusted input in `+page.server.ts` actions, `+server.ts` handlers, and remote functions.

```ts
import { z } from 'zod';
import { fail } from '@sveltejs/kit';

const signInSchema = z.object({
	email: z.email(),
	password: z.string().min(8),
	name: z.string().min(1).optional()
});

export const actions = {
	signUp: async ({ request }) => {
		const raw = Object.fromEntries(await request.formData());
		const parsed = signInSchema.safeParse(raw);

		if (!parsed.success) {
			return fail(400, {
				message: parsed.error.issues[0]?.message ?? 'Invalid input',
				errors: parsed.error.flatten().fieldErrors
			});
		}

		const { email, password, name } = parsed.data;
		// ...
	}
};
```

## Rules

- Use `safeParse` in request handlers; throw only for programmer errors
- Share schemas in `$lib/schemas/` when used by client + server
- Infer types: `type SignIn = z.infer<typeof signInSchema>`
- Prefer `z.email()`, `z.uuid()`, `z.coerce.number()` over loose `z.string()` where applicable
- Return `fail(status, { errors })` so SvelteKit forms can show field errors
